<subSubSection id="A2A86574FFC3FFB9749DF9F8BE53F93A" pageId="11" pageNumber="541" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EA0D36FFFFC3FFB9749DF9F8BE53F93A" blockId="11.[151,1436,1609,1742]" pageId="11" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis id="D8C6EAEDFFC3FFB9749DF9F8B80EF9DE" bold="true" box="[199,588,1609,1634]" pageId="11" pageNumber="541">Distribution and natural history.</emphasis>
The species is known only from the Central Province of 
<collectingCountry id="92A5766FFFC3FFB9709DF9F8BF75F9DE" box="[1223,1335,1609,1634]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="11" pageNumber="541">
Sri 
<taxonomicName id="2DB24D7CFFC3FFB970B4F9F8BF75F9DE" box="[1262,1335,1609,1634]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanka">Lanka</taxonomicName>
</collectingCountry>
, where it was collected in forest leaf litter at elevations ranging from 
<quantity id="2D4A9B1AFFC3FFB9776EF9DCB99FF93A" box="[820,989,1645,1670]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="541" unit="m" value="875.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="750.0">750 to 1000 m</quantity>
.a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A2A86574FFC3FFB9749DF920BB94F972" pageId="11" pageNumber="541" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="EA0D36FFFFC3FFB9749DF920BB94F972" blockId="11.[151,1436,1609,1742]" pageId="11" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis id="D8C6EAEDFFC3FFB9749DF920BB0CF916" bold="true" box="[199,334,1681,1706]" pageId="11" pageNumber="541">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is based on the name of the island, treated as a Latin singular noun in apposition, nominative case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
